The explosives storage magazines market is regulated by various government agencies such as the Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) in the U.S. and the Health and Safety Executive (HSE) in the U.K., which set safety standards and guidelines for the storage and handling of explosives.

9. What are the different applications of explosives storage magazines?
The explosives storage magazines are used for storing explosives and detonators used in mining, construction, military, and pyrotechnics industries.

